comment._content: I am not 100% sure this is the 1900 Cannibal visit, as the 'Möwe' was part of the German Pacific Squadron earlier than 1895, along with the 'Bussard' which was discovered on Flickr a few years ago (hence my very limited knowledge) - [http://www.flickr.com/photos/powerhouse_museum/3229538689/]MegaZoomable at from.ph/381246

comment._content:
The German Navy records are usually incredibly comprehensive,  but I have not had a great deal of success with this 'Möwe',  because there was a later and more famous WW1 'raider' ship of the same name.

Another work in progress ...
